accountingContextForTokenOf(uint256,addr.details: Accounting contexts are set up in `addDefaultPool(...)`.

params.projectId: The ID of the project to get the accounting context for.
params.token: The address of the token to get the accounting context for.

returns._0: A `JBAccountingContext` containing the accounting context for the project ID and token.

accountingContextsOf(uint256).details: This includes both project-specific and generic accounting contexts, with the project-specific contexts         taking precedence.

params.projectId: The ID of the project to get the accounting contexts for.

returns._0: An array of `JBAccountingContext` containing the accounting contexts for the project ID.

addDefaultPool(uint256,address,address).details: This does not set the twap parameters, they *must* be set using `addTwapParamsFor` (if not, the twap duration will be 0 which will cause the swap to revert).

params.pool: The Uniswap V3 pool to set as the default for the specified token.
params.projectId: The ID of the project to set the default pool for. The project 0 acts as a catch-all, where non-set pools are defaulted to.
params.token: The address of the token to set the default pool for.

addToBalanceOf(uint256,address,uint256,b.details: This function handles the token in transfer, potentially swaps the tokens to the desired output token, and then adds the swapped tokens to the project's balance in the specified terminal.

params.amount: The amount of tokens being paid in.
params.memo: A memo to pass along to the emitted event.
params.metadata: Bytes in `JBMetadataResolver`'s format which can contain additional data for the swap and adding to balance.
params.projectId: The ID of the project for which funds are being accepted and added to its balance.
params.shouldReturnHeldFees: A boolean to indicate whether held fees should be returned.
params.token: The address of the token being paid in.

params.projectId: The ID of the project to set the TWAP-based quote rules for.
params.secondsAgo: The period of time over which the TWAP is calculated, in seconds.
params.slippageTolerance: The maximum spread allowed between the amount received and the TWAP (as a fraction out of `SLIPPAGE_DENOMINATOR`).

params.projectId: The ID of the project to retrieve the default pool for.
params.tokenIn: The address of the token to retrieve the default pool for.

returns.pool: The default pool for the token, or the overall default pool for the token if the

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.amount: The amount of tokens being paid in, as a fixed point number with the same amount of decimals as the `token`. If `token` is the native token, `amount` is ignored and `msg.value` is used in its place.
params.beneficiary: The beneficiary address to pass along to the other terminal. If the other terminal mints tokens, for example, they will be minted for this address.
params.memo: A memo to pass along to the emitted event.
params.metadata: Bytes in `JBMetadataResolver`'s format which can contain a quote from the user/client. The quote should contain a minimum amount of tokens to receive from the swap and the pool to use. This metadata is also passed to the other terminal's emitted event, as well as its data hook and pay hook if applicable.
params.minReturnedTokens: The minimum number of project tokens expected in return, as a fixed point number with the same number of decimals as the other terminal. This value will be passed along to the other terminal.
params.projectId: The ID of the project being paid.
params.token: The address of the token being paid in.

returns._0: The number of tokens received from the swap, as a fixed point number with the same amount of decimals as that token.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.interfaceId: The ID of the interface to check for adherance to.

returns._0: A flag indicating if the provided interface ID is supported.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params.projectId: The ID of the project to retrieve TWAP parameters for.

returns.secondsAgo: The period of time in the past to calculate the TWAP from.
returns.slippageTolerance: The maximum allowed slippage tolerance when calculating the TWAP, as a fraction out of `SLIPPAGE_DENOMINATOR`.

uniswapV3SwapCallback(int256,int256,byte.details: This function has no access control, care should be taken to ensure that:      - terminal balance is always be 0 between tx (this callback can only be used to sweep accidental leftovers)      - callback cannot pull user funds via a preexisting allowance

params.amount0Delta: The amount of token 0 being used for the swap.
params.amount1Delta: The amount of token 1 being used for the swap.
params.data: Data passed in by the swap operation.

DEFAULT_PROJECT_ID().notice: The ID to store default values in.

DIRECTORY().notice: The directory of terminals and controllers for `PROJECTS`.

PROJECTS().notice: Mints ERC-721s that represent project ownership and transfers.

SLIPPAGE_DENOMINATOR().notice: The denominator used when calculating TWAP slippage tolerance values.

TOKEN_OUT().notice: The token which flows out of this terminal (JBConstants.NATIVE_TOKEN for the chain native token)

WETH().notice: The ERC-20 wrapper for the native token.

accountingContextForTokenOf(uint256,addr.notice: Get the accounting context for the specified project ID and token.

accountingContextsOf(uint256).notice: Return all the accounting contexts for a specified project ID.

addAccountingContextsFor(uint256,address.notice: Empty implementation to satisfy the interface. Accounting contexts are set in `addDefaultPool(...)`.

addDefaultPool(uint256,address,address).notice: Set a project's default pool and accounting context for the specified token. Only the project's owner, an address with `MODIFY_DEFAULT_POOL` permission from the owner or the terminal owner can call this function.

addToBalanceOf(uint256,address,uint256,b.notice: Accepts funds for a given project, swaps them if necessary, and adds them to the project's balance in the specified terminal.

addTwapParamsFor(uint256,address,uint32,.notice: Set the specified project's rules for calculating a quote based on the TWAP. Only the project's owner or an address with `MODIFY_TWAP_PARAMS` permission from the owner  or the terminal owner can call this function.

currentSurplusOf(uint256,uint256,uint256.notice: Empty implementation to satisfy the interface. This terminal has no surplus.

getPoolFor(uint256,address).notice: Returns the default pool for a given project and token or, if a project has no default pool for the         token, the overal default pool for the token

migrateBalanceOf(uint256,address,address.notice: Empty implementation to satisfy the interface.

pay(uint256,address,uint256,address,uint.notice: Pay a project by swapping the incoming tokens for tokens that one of the project's other terminals accepts, passing along the funds received from the swap and the specified parameters.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Indicates if this contract adheres to the specified interface.

twapParamsOf(uint256,address).notice: Returns the default twap parameters for a given pool project.

uniswapV3SwapCallback(int256,int256,byte.notice: The Uniswap v3 pool callback where the token transfer is expected to happen.
